For {= channel_relationship =}+ public pump-room equipment channel relationships, name the equipment family, manufacturer/brand, and channel partner, and for each of the {= source_side =} relationship sides supply a relationship-substantiating source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL per side).

A relationship should involve pumps, valves/actuation, compressed air, vacuum or blower equipment, filtration/strainers, PP-RCT or HDPE piping, or adjacent pump-room mechanical equipment. The channel partner may be a distributor, representative, dealer, stocking distributor, factory-authorized service center, product-line partner, or comparable public channel party. The relationship ought to be between distinct organizations or brands, not a same-company alias, end-customer reference, vendor-registration entry, contact-only listing, or generic marketplace presence.

The relationship sides of interest, which we refer to as `source_side`, are:
- `manufacturer_ack`: a manufacturer/brand-side source acknowledging the channel partner, territory, distributor/rep/dealer/service status, or equivalent public role.
- `channel_claim`: a channel-partner-side source naming the manufacturer/brand or exact product line/family and stating the partner's role, line, representation, service, stocking, or capability claim.

Florida presence is source-stated context, not a universal eligibility gate. A source may state a Florida office, territory, distributor/rep status, or service area; generic national availability is not Florida evidence. This task is public provenance only: RFQ preparation, pricing, contact enrichment, supplier ranking or recommendation, engineering fitness, safety/compliance adequacy, and procurement advice are out of scope.

Requirements:
- The page should communicate that it is on the correct source side: manufacturer/brand-owned, manufacturer-group-owned, official locator/channel page, or public manufacturer letter for `manufacturer_ack`; partner-owned website, product page, line card, equipment page, or partner PDF for `channel_claim`.
- The page must explicitly connect the submitted manufacturer/brand and channel partner to the same public relationship.
- The page must expose concrete source-stated relationship wording, such as distributor, representative, dealer, service center, stocking line, represents, carries, preferred source, or a comparable role/line phrase.
- The page must tie the relationship to the submitted pump-room equipment family, not merely to company existence, procurement registration, contact information, or a standards/listing claim.
